      <h2>What Comes Next</h2>

      <p>A 30-second dead hang marks the transition from beginner to <a href="/intermediate-deadhang/">intermediate level</a>. Two paths open up from here.</p>

      <h3>Path 1: 8-Week Intermediate Program</h3>

      <p>The <a href="/8-week-program/">8-week intermediate dead hang program</a> pushes your hold to 60-90 seconds. It adds a fourth weekly session and introduces underhand and neutral grip rotations. This is the direct next step for most trainees.</p>

      <h3>Path 2: Maintain and Integrate</h3>

      <p>Keep your 30-second hold with 2 sessions per week at 3 sets each. Integrate dead hangs as a warm-up for climbing, CrossFit, or general gym training. Return to the <a href="/training-programs/">training programs page</a> when ready to progress further.</p>

